				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have recently added a Driud for a playing companion to my beastlord, and have a few questions.  
<br />

<br />
I know that the formula is 1.5X your lower chars level in order to gain xp while grouped with the other char.  What I am uncertain is what the % split on the xp division.  I have taken off 2 of the last 3 years playing, and prior to that time, I did not play often enough to keep up with the changes made.  
<br />

<br />
Does the higher level char still take the same % split as the level differential, or has that changed, and if so, at what time would be a good point to group.  My Beastlord is currently 52.  
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance for any comments..</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
