				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Does the higher level char still take the same % split as the level differential, or has that changed</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
As far as I understand it your understanding is also correct in this respect - at least as a starting point.
<br />

<br />
Consequently, the majority of the xp will go to the higher level toon. However, the higher level toon will be negatively impacted by the 6 level rule and the light blue mobs rule. I dont know the exact formula here, but you suffer an xp penalty if the mob you hunt is more than 6 levels below your own level and I also think you suffer an even higher xp penalty when the mob becomes light blue (can anyone confirm this?).
<br />

<br />
What all this sums up to is that grouping a level 43 with a level 65 in order to hunt light blue mobs is a bad idea. The majority of the xp goes to the higher level toon, but then the higher level toon suffers a penalty and a lot of xp points is actually "wasted". So leave the level 43 character outside of group when you PL.
<br />

<br />
Finally I also think that there is some kind of "cap" on the xp a lower level toon can get from a certain mob. If you allow a level 4 toon to get the solo kill on a level 40 mob it should in theory instantly get several levels, but it doesnt.
<br />

<br />
Bari</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
